   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the screws and the bottom front plate from the transformer
cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Transformer Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50ditransf_prepareremoveplateforpower_w120mm_0000161923.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the bottom gland plate in the transformer cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Transformer Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50ditransf_preparebottomentry_w120mm_0000161953.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drill holes and install conduits for bypass cables in the
bottom gland plate. Conduits are not provided.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <hazardstatement type="danger">
                  <messagepanel>
                     <typeofhazard>Hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
                     <howtoavoid>Do not drill or cut holes for cables or conduits with
the gland plate installed and do not drill or cut holes in close proximity
to the UPS.</howtoavoid>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the bottom gland plate in the transformer cabinet.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
